The paper deals with optimization problems on hypergraphs, which are a natural generalization of graphs. The Densest k-Subhypergraph problem is a variant of the Densest k-Subgraph problem, which is a well-known problem in approximation algorithms and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also introduces a new problem called Minimum p-Union, which is related to set cover and falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The authors provide approximation algorithms for both problems, which involves techniques from graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Overall, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which is a broad category that encompasses many subfields of computer science.
